com.ibm.util.merge

Class Config

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.util.merge.Config

  • public class Config
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides configuration information for the Merge Utility You can optionally load a configuration with one of the provided load functions. Implemented as a singleton with static convenience methods
    Author:
    Mike Storey

      • Config

        public Config()
       throws MergeException
        Provide a default configuration. If the enviornment variable idmu-config exists it is parsed as a json configuration value. If the config environment variable does not exist, all defaults are provided.

      • getEnv

        public java.lang.String getEnv(java.lang.String name)
                        throws MergeException
        Abstraction of Environment access. Will leverage an entry from the local Environment hashmap property. Environment Variables prefixed with "VCAP:" will be treated as entries in the VCAP_SERVICES environment variable. You can provide environment values by adding entries to the envVars hashMap
        Parameters:
        name - The environment variable
        Returns:
        The environment value
        Throws:
        MergeException - on Processing Errors
